President Trump expressed his condolences to the Bush family on the passing of former First Lady Barbara Bush. He praised her as a titan in American life and a tireless champion for literacy. He also thanked the service members from the US, France, and the UK involved in the strikes on Syrian chemical weapons targets. He discussed his upcoming meeting with Kim Jong-un to discuss the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and expressed hope for a successful outcome. President Trump and Prime Minister Abe of Japan discussed the North Korean issue and the US-Japan alliance. They agreed to continue their effort towards the resolution of the abduction issue and to strengthen economic ties. They also announced the initiation of talks for free, fair, and reciprocal trade deals. President Trump mentioned the possibility of removing aluminum and steel tariffs if a new trade deal is reached with Japan.